commitResults.messageTitle: Check magnitude of amount in change quantity command
Add constraints to quantity and amount values
commitResults.messageBody:
Quantity and amount values are capped to a maximum of 2 decimal places
and cannot go beyond the double range in Java. As such, the regex to
check for a valid format of the values is modified.

Test cases are also added to StringUtilTest and ParserUtilTest to check
for valid values.

thus fixed.

commitResults.messageBody: The expiry date format is now in DD-MM-YYYY where the day and month are stored as 2 digits while the year is stored as 4 digits.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bug where no error message shown for huge amount
commitResults.messageBody:
When a user is trying to change the quantity of a food item by a huge
amount more than 999,999, the app will display an error message.

commitResults.messageBody:
Error messages for invalid expiry dates have been standardised.

The year of expiry date is now constrained between 2020 and 2120, both
inclusive.

More test cases for expiry date have been added.

The quantity value must now be more than 0.00 but less than or
equal to 100,000.00.

More test cases for quantity are added.

The amount value must now be a non-zero signed number more than
-100,000.00 and less than +100,000.00.

More test cases to check for the range of amount value are added.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix error message for invalid expiry date
commitResults.messageBody:
The error message asks user to input a valid date if an invalid date
with the correct formatting is enterd e.g. 29-02-2021.
